metadata.description:
The art is programmatically drawn using basic shapes, math, random using p5js.

press 'd' or '7' to save in high quality and 
press 'f' to see art in full screen.

metadata.name: Galactica #7
metadata.description:
Galactica shows us the landscapes of a distant exoplanetary system made up of 10 planets.
Standing on one of these planets with its particular geomorphology, we may see faraway galaxies, natural satellites and/or another planet in the sky.

The combination of the various features can give life to up to 415,000 different versions, taking into account the differences not related to features the versions rise to about 12 billion.

Press "s" to get a 2000x2000 pixels jpg.

Generative artwork by Gandhiavelli, @gandhiavelli. Made with p5js in 2022.
License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Tranquility #69
metadata.description:
Nature is like freshing water that purifies our minds. In it, we can shake off all the noise of daily life and calm down our minds, and the tranquility of nature gives us a moment of healing. this moment gives us the feeling that time has stopped, and it gives us new energy and peace.

I hope this work will give you the least sense of tranquility.

--

Features:
- View: Sea / Hill / Field
- Palette: Spring / Summer / Fall / Winter / Blue / Red
- Flowers: True / False
- Rill: True / False

--

Press "s" in live mode to download the rendered image as a png file. 

Made with p5js and passion
By thion, January 2024

metadata.name: CA Panico #152
metadata.description:
Third chapter of the trilogy dedicated to Stephen Wolfram's cellular automata.
 
Compared to CA Vista and CA Monti, CA Panico aims to further abstract the concept of landscape using CA rules in a more massive way.

The great variety of CA rules that controls the coloring and textures, noise influence, division into quadrants, chance of having glitches and outages all combined with 25 palettes and 5 different formats means that the outputs will be very varied and peculiar.

Press 'S' to download, you can zoom downloaded output to enjoy all the details.

metadata.name: Anfractuous #492
metadata.description: The title is quite literally a visual description of the work, as anfractuous means: characterized by windings and turnings; sinuous; circuitous. With this project I aimed to strike a balance between easily recognizable smooth large scale forms and the small fragmented details that populate these forms.

metadata.name: Human Echoes #29
metadata.description:
Human Echoes is a generative art collection that explores the resonating patterns and forms of human existence through the lens of isometric and geometric abstraction. Each piece reflects the idea that every human experience, thought, and action reverberates like an echo, leaving a trace that blends into the greater structure of reality. By using precise geometric shapes and isometric perspectives, the collection draws parallels between the complex yet ordered patterns in both human nature and the mathematical world. "Human Echoes" invites viewers to reflect on the harmony between individuality and the collective, as well as the cyclical nature of human impact over time.

*Save image: press 'W' to save the current image as a PNG.
